
# 2026-06-27 10:59:19.938830
+# Brief: Add Kokoro Health Check and Fallback to KokoroProvider
+
+## Goal
+KokoroProvider.swift automatically detects when Kokoro TTS service is unavailable and falls back to ElevenLabsProvider without user intervention.
+
+## Context
+- **Repo:** `~/Projects/sonique-mac` (SoniqueBar macOS app)
+- **File to modify:** `SoniqueBar/Providers/KokoroProvider.swift`
+- **Related file:** `SoniqueBar/Providers/ElevenLabsProvider.swift` (fallback target)
+- **Pattern:** Similar to other providers in `SoniqueBar/Providers/` directory
+- **Current behavior:** Kokoro failures likely crash or hang the voice output
+- **Requirements from CLAUDE.md:**
+  - Read Apple Speech/AVFoundation docs before modifying audio code
+  - Test changes by running the app and speaking to Quinn
+  - Follow Swift naming conventions in existing codebase
+
+## Steps
+1. **Research:** Read current KokoroProvider.swift implementation to understand initialization and TTS flow
+2. **Design health check:** 
+   - Add `isAvailable()` method that attempts a lightweight connection to Kokoro service
+   - Cache availability status with 5-minute TTL to avoid repeated checks
+   - Log health check results for debugging
+3. **Implement fallback:**
+   - Modify `speak()` method to call `isAvailable()` before attempting Kokoro TTS
+   - If unavailable, route to `ElevenLabsProvider.speak()` with same text/options
+   - Log fallback events: "⚠️ Kokoro unavailable, falling back to ElevenLabs"
+4. **Test:**
+   - Build app in Xcode
+   - With Kokoro running: verify voice output uses Kokoro
+   - Stop Kokoro service: verify automatic fallback to ElevenLabs
+   - Restart Kokoro: verify it recovers after 5-minute cache expires
+
+## Dependencies
+- **Files that must exist:**
+  - `~/Projects/sonique-mac/SoniqueBar/Providers/KokoroProvider.swift`
+  - `~/Projects/sonique-mac/SoniqueBar/Providers/ElevenLabsProvider.swift`
+- **Services:** ElevenLabsProvider must be configured with valid API key (fallback target)
+- **Xcode:** macOS development environment with Swift toolchain
+
+## Potential Issues
+1. **Kokoro connection timeout too long** → Use 3-second timeout for health check
+2. **Fallback causes voice mismatch** → Log when fallback occurs so user knows why voice changed
+3. **Cache prevents recovery** → Implement cache invalidation on successful Kokoro response
+
+## Expected Output
+- Modified: `SoniqueBar/Providers/KokoroProvider.swift` with health check + fallback logic
+- Git commit with descriptive message
+- No build errors in Xcode
+
+## Success Criteria
+- [ ] `xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build` exits 0
+- [ ] With Kokoro down, TTS request succeeds using ElevenLabs (no crash/hang)
+- [ ] Console logs show "⚠️ Kokoro unavailable, falling back to ElevenLabs"
+- [ ] With Kokoro up, TTS uses Kokoro (logs show "✓ Kokoro health check passed")
+
+## Verification
+```bash
+cd ~/Projects/sonique-mac
+xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build
+grep -q "isAvailable" SoniqueBar/Providers/KokoroProvider.swift
+grep -q "fallback" SoniqueBar/Providers/KokoroProvider.swift
+```
+
+## Security Review
+- **Threats:** None (internal service health check)
+- **Secrets:** No new credentials required
+- **Network:** Health check uses existing Kokoro service connection
+
+## Functional Test
+1. Launch SoniqueBar
+2. Say "Hey Quinn, tell me a joke"
+3. Verify voice output plays (using ElevenLabs if Kokoro down)
+4. Check Console.app logs for health check status
+
+## Recovery
+If health check logic breaks voice output entirely:
+- Revert to simple try/catch around Kokoro calls
+- Mark NHR with diagnostic: "Kokoro health check broke existing flow"
+
+## Rollback
+```bash
+cd ~/Projects/sonique-mac
+git revert HEAD
+xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build
+```

