# 2026-06-27 11:27:39.210052
+# Brief: Create PermissionsManager.swift with TCC Status Detection
+
+## Goal
+Create `PermissionsManager.swift` that provides real-time status detection for all macOS system permissions (TCC) required by SoniqueBar.
+
+## Context
+- **Repo:** `~/Projects/sonique-mac`
+- **New file:** `SoniqueBar/Services/PermissionsManager.swift`
+- **Permissions to track:**
+  - Screen Recording (AVCaptureDevice)
+  - Microphone (AVCaptureDevice)
+  - Calendar (EventKit)
+  - Reminders (EventKit)
+  - Accessibility (AXIsProcessTrusted)
+  - Full Disk Access (file access test)
+- **Current state:** App may crash or silently fail when permissions missing
+- **Pattern:** Singleton manager accessible from any view
+- **Prerequisites completed:** Apple's TCC documentation has been reviewed (see Dependencies section for URLs)
+
+## Dependencies
+- **Files that must exist:**
+  - `~/Projects/sonique-mac/SoniqueBar/Info.plist` (for usage descriptions)
+  - `~/Projects/sonique-mac/SoniqueBar/SoniqueBar.entitlements`
+- **Frameworks:** AVFoundation, EventKit, ApplicationServices (for AX APIs)
+- **Documentation:** 
+  - AVFoundation auth: https://developer.apple.com/documentation/avfoundation/capture_setup/requesting_authorization_to_capture_and_save_media
+  - EventKit auth: https://developer.apple.com/documentation/eventkit/accessing_the_event_store
+  - Verified current as of macOS 12.3+ (project deployment target)
+
+## Steps
+1. **Create file structure:**
+   - Create `SoniqueBar/Services/PermissionsManager.swift`
+   - Import required frameworks: Foundation, AVFoundation, EventKit, ApplicationServices
+
+2. **Define types:**
+   - Enum `PermissionType`: `.screenRecording, .microphone, .calendar, .reminders, .accessibility, .fullDiskAccess`
+   - Enum `PermissionStatus`: `.granted, .denied, .notDetermined, .restricted`
+
+3. **Implement singleton:**
+   - Class `PermissionsManager` with `shared` static property
+   - Method: `status(for: PermissionType) -> PermissionStatus`
+   - Method: `requestPermission(for: PermissionType, completion: (Bool) -> Void)`
+   - Observable properties for SwiftUI integration (if using @Published)
+
+4. **Implement permission checks:**
+   - Screen Recording: `AVCaptureDevice.authorizationStatus(for: .video)`
+   - Microphone: `AVCaptureDevice.authorizationStatus(for: .audio)`
+   - Calendar: `EKEventStore.authorizationStatus(for: .event)`
+   - Reminders: `EKEventStore.authorizationStatus(for: .reminder)`
+   - Accessibility: `AXIsProcessTrusted()`
+   - Full Disk Access: Test read `~/Library/Safari/` (protected location)
+
+5. **Add logging:**
+   - Log each permission status check
+   - Use structured logging format: `[PermissionsManager][PermissionType] status`
+
+6. **Update Info.plist if needed:**
+   - Verify usage description strings exist for each permission
+   - If missing, add them with clear explanations
+
+## Potential Issues
+1. **Status checks use async callbacks** → Use completion handlers or async/await
+2. **Accessibility requires running app** → Document this in code comments
+3. **Full Disk Access has no direct API** → Use file access test as proxy
+
+## Expected Output
+- New file: `SoniqueBar/Services/PermissionsManager.swift` (~200-250 lines)
+- Modified (if needed): `Info.plist` with usage description strings
+- Git commit
+- Build succeeds without errors
+
+## Success Criteria
+- [ ] `xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build` exits 0
+- [ ] `PermissionsManager.shared.status(for:)` returns correct status for each permission type
+- [ ] Console shows permission status logs on first call
+- [ ] File exists at expected path
+
+## Verification
+```bash
+cd ~/Projects/sonique-mac
+xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build
+test -f SoniqueBar/Services/PermissionsManager.swift
+grep -q "PermissionType" SoniqueBar/Services/PermissionsManager.swift
+grep -q "PermissionStatus" SoniqueBar/Services/PermissionsManager.swift
+grep -q "class PermissionsManager" SoniqueBar/Services/PermissionsManager.swift
+```
+
+## Security Review
+- **Threats:** None (reads permission status, doesn't grant anything)
+- **Privacy:** Usage description strings must explain why each permission is needed
+- **Best practice:** Never request permissions until user action requires it
+
+## Functional Test
+1. Build and launch SoniqueBar
+2. Open Console.app, filter for "PermissionsManager"
+3. Trigger permission check (e.g., from Settings view or on startup)
+4. Verify log shows: "✓ Screen Recording: granted" or "⚠️ Screen Recording: denied"
+5. Open System Settings > Privacy & Security > Screen Recording
+6. Toggle SoniqueBar permission
+7. Re-check in app, verify status updates correctly
+
+## Recovery
+If permission checks crash the app:
+- Wrap all TCC API calls in do-catch or guard statements
+- Return `.notDetermined` on any error
+- Mark NHR with diagnostic: "TCC API crash on [PermissionType]"
+
+## Rollback
+```bash
+cd ~/Projects/sonique-mac
+git revert HEAD
+xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build
+```
+
+## Notes
+- Apple's TCC APIs vary across macOS versions - code targets macOS 12.3+ per project settings
+- Some permissions (like Accessibility) require app restart to take effect
+- Full Disk Access requires app to be signed and notarized for real TCC enforcement
+- Code examples from Apple docs show proper usage patterns for each permission type

