+# Brief: Remove ScreenAwarenessService and CLI Screenshot Logic
+
+## Goal
+Remove deprecated ScreenAwarenessService.swift and any CLI-based screenshot logic after LiveScreenCapture.swift is verified working.
+
+## Context
+- **Repo:** `~/Projects/sonique-mac`
+- **Files to delete:** `SoniqueBar/Services/ScreenAwarenessService.swift` (if exists)
+- **Files to search:** All Swift files referencing ScreenAwarenessService
+- **Prerequisite:** LiveScreenCapture must be wired and working (task #1005675)
+- **Why:** Consolidating to single screen capture system
+
+## Dependencies
+- **Must be completed first:** Task #1005675 (LiveScreenCapture integration)
+- **Must verify:** LiveScreenCapture successfully capturing screenshots
+
+## Steps
+1. **Search for all references:**
+   ```bash
+   cd ~/Projects/sonique-mac
+   grep -r "ScreenAwarenessService" SoniqueBar/ --include="*.swift"
+   grep -r "screencapture" SoniqueBar/ --include="*.swift"  # CLI tool usage
+   ```
+
+2. **Remove import statements:**
+   - Find all files importing ScreenAwarenessService
+   - Remove `import ScreenAwarenessService` lines
+
+3. **Remove initialization code:**
+   - Search for `.shared`, `.start()`, `.stop()` calls
+   - Remove initialization in app entry point
+   - Remove any configuration or setup code
+
+4. **Remove usage code:**
+   - Find method calls to the service
+   - Replace with LiveScreenCapture equivalents OR remove if redundant
+   - Check for any delegates, callbacks, or observers
+
+5. **Delete service file:**
+   ```bash
+   rm SoniqueBar/Services/ScreenAwarenessService.swift
+   ```
+
+6. **Search for CLI screenshot usage:**
+   ```bash
+   grep -r "screencapture" SoniqueBar/ --include="*.swift"
+   grep -r "Process()" SoniqueBar/ | grep -i screen
+   ```
+
+7. **Remove CLI screenshot logic:**
+   - Remove shell command invocations of `screencapture`
+   - Remove temporary file handling for screenshots
+   - Replace with LiveScreenCapture API calls
+
+8. **Clean up project:**
+   - Remove file references from Xcode project if needed
+   - Verify no broken imports remain
+
+## Potential Issues
+1. **Other features depend on ScreenAwarenessService** → Migrate them to LiveScreenCapture
+2. **File doesn't exist** → Verify via search first, not an error
+3. **Build breaks after removal** → Check for missed references
+
+## Expected Output
+- Deleted: `SoniqueBar/Services/ScreenAwarenessService.swift` (if exists)
+- Modified: Files that previously imported/used the service
+- Clean build with no references to old system
+
+## Success Criteria
+- [ ] No file exists at `SoniqueBar/Services/ScreenAwarenessService.swift`
+- [ ] `grep -r "ScreenAwarenessService" SoniqueBar/` returns 0 matches
+- [ ] `grep -r "screencapture" SoniqueBar/ --include="*.swift"` returns 0 matches (or only comments)
+- [ ] `xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build` exits 0
+
+## Verification
+```bash
+cd ~/Projects/sonique-mac
+
+# Verify file deleted
+! test -f SoniqueBar/Services/ScreenAwarenessService.swift
+
+# Verify no references remain
+! grep -r "ScreenAwarenessService" SoniqueBar/ --include="*.swift"
+! grep -r "screencapture" SoniqueBar/ --include="*.swift" | grep -v "^[[:space:]]*#\|^[[:space:]]*//"
+
+# Verify build succeeds
+xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build
+```
+
+## QA Checklist
+- [ ] q1: File deleted → `! test -f SoniqueBar/Services/ScreenAwarenessService.swift`
+- [ ] q2: No imports remain → `! grep "import.*ScreenAwarenessService"`
+- [ ] q3: No CLI screencapture → `! grep "screencapture" SoniqueBar/**/*.swift`
+- [ ] q4: Build succeeds → `xcodebuild build && echo $?`
+
+## Security Review
+- **Threats:** None (code removal)
+- **Cleanup:** Verify no leftover temp files or screenshots
+
+## Functional Test
+1. Build and run SoniqueBar after deletion
+2. Trigger screenshot capture via LiveScreenCapture
+3. Verify screenshots still work correctly
+4. Check Console.app for no errors about missing services
+
+## Recovery
+If build breaks after removal:
+- Check for missed import statements
+- Verify LiveScreenCapture has equivalent functionality
+- Mark NHR with diagnostic: "Build failed after ScreenAwarenessService removal"
+
+## Rollback
+```bash
+cd ~/Projects/sonique-mac
+git revert HEAD
+xcodebuild -project SoniqueBar.xcodeproj -scheme SoniqueBar build
+```
+
+## Notes
+- If ScreenAwarenessService.swift doesn't exist, this task is already complete
+- Verify LiveScreenCapture provides all needed functionality before deleting
+- Check for any CLI `screencapture` usage outside of the service file
+- Consider removing any related configuration keys from UserDefaults
+

