+## QA Checklist
+- [ ] q1: DiagnosticSnapshot → `grep "struct DiagnosticSnapshot"`
+- [ ] q2: sendDiagnosticToMac → `grep "func sendDiagnosticToMac"`
+- [ ] q3: Error capture → `grep "DiagnosticSnapshot" HTTPClient.swift`
+- [ ] q4: Infinite loop guard → `grep "/diagnose" HTTPClient.swift | grep -v "sendDiagnosticToMac\|guard"`
+- [ ] q5: Build succeeds → `xcodebuild build && echo $?`
+
+## Security Review
+- **Threats:**
+  - Sensitive data in error messages
+  - Network traffic interception
+- **Mitigations:**
+  - Use HTTPS if Mac supports it
+  - Redact sensitive headers (Authorization, API keys)
+  - Local network only (no internet transit)
+- **Privacy:** Error messages may contain user data — sanitize before sending
+
+## Functional Test
+1. Ensure Mac running with POST /diagnose endpoint
+2. Build and run Sonique iOS app
+3. Configure Mac IP address (or use discovery)
+4. Trigger network error (e.g., stop Mac server)
+5. Attempt voice command
+6. Verify diagnostic sent:
+   ```bash
+   # On Mac
+   tail -f ~/Library/Application\ Support/SoniqueBar/diagnostics/*.json
+   ```
+7. Check iOS console:
+   ```
+   [Diagnostics] Capturing snapshot for error: ...
+   [Diagnostics] Snapshot sent to Mac
+   ```
+8. Verify diagnostic file created on Mac
+9. Test guard against infinite loop:
+   - Break /diagnose endpoint
+   - Verify diagnostic send fails but doesn't retry infinitely
+
+## Recovery
+If diagnostic capture crashes app:
+- Wrap JSON encoding in try-catch
+- Add nil checks for all optional fields
+- Mark NHR with diagnostic: "DiagnosticSnapshot capture crashed"
+
+## Rollback
+```bash
+cd ~/Projects/sonique-ios
+git revert HEAD
+xcodebuild -project Sonique.xcodeproj -scheme Sonique build
+```
+
+## Notes
+- Mac IP discovery: consider using Bonjour (_sonique._tcp.local)
+- Rate limiting: store last diagnostic send timestamp in memory
+- Don't send diagnostics for cancelled requests (user-initiated)
+- Consider adding diagnostic UI in iOS app settings to view sent diagnostics
+- ISO8601 timestamp format with Z suffix (UTC)
+- Device model examples: "iPhone14,2" (iPhone 13 Pro), "iPad13,1" (iPad Pro)
